---
layout: base.njk
title: Gallery — Bucks County CuriARTsity
description: A rotating record of fine art, antiques, and curiosities that have passed through Bucks County CuriARTsity in Lambertville, NJ.
---
{# ABOUTME: Gallery index — renders the `gallery` collection (one markdown file per piece) as catalogue lots. #}

<section class="page-head">
  <p class="hero__eyebrow">Pl. IV — The Collection</p>
  <h1 class="page-head__title">Recently Passed<br>Through These Doors</h1>
  <p class="hero__lead">A rotating record of pieces that found new homes. New finds appear here
    as they cross the threshold — so it is never quite the same twice.</p>
</section>

<section class="movement">
  {% if collections.gallery | length %}
  <div class="lots">
    {%- for item in collections.gallery | reverse %}
    <article class="lot{% if item.data.sold %} lot--sold{% endif %}">
      <a class="lot__media" href="{{ item.url }}">
        {% if item.data.image %}
          <img src="{{ item.data.image }}" alt="{{ item.data.title }}" loading="lazy">
        {% else %}
          <span class="lot__plate">Pl.</span>
        {% endif %}
        {% if item.data.sold %}<span class="sold-stamp">Sold</span>{% endif %}
      </a>
      <div class="lot__meta">
        <span class="lot__no">No. {{ loop.index }}</span>
        <h2 class="lot__title"><a href="{{ item.url }}">{{ item.data.title }}</a></h2>
        <p class="lot__detail">{{ item.data.medium }}{% if item.data.year %} · {{ item.data.year }}{% endif %}</p>
      </div>
    </article>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
  {% else %}
  <p class="prose prose--lead">The catalogue is being photographed. Check back soon.</p>
  {% endif %}
</section>
